# Flue Zoe Telegram channel — LAB ONLY. Copy to .env; never commit a real .env.

# --- Telegram ---
# Bot token. Reuse Hermes's existing bot (it's paused, so no conflict); the bot
# moves from Hermes to here when this starts polling. From @BotFather otherwise.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# Comma-separated Telegram user IDs allowed to talk to Zoe. FAIL-CLOSED: empty =
# nobody gets through. This is a COARSE gate (defence in depth); real per-user
# identity comes from account linking below. Your id is in ~/.hermes/.env as
# TELEGRAM_HOME_CHANNEL.
TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS=

# --- Zoe's brain: zoe-data's /api/chat (the SAME pipeline voice + touch use) ---
# This channel does NOT call the local voice Gemma on :11434 — it asks zoe-data,
# which owns intent routing, tools, memory and persona. Default is correct on the
# Jetson; point elsewhere only to test against another zoe-data endpoint.
# ZOE_BRAIN_URL is kept as a back-compat alias for ZOE_DATA_URL.
ZOE_DATA_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000

# --- Account linking (telegram_id → real Zoe user + their memory) ---
# Shared secret for zoe-data's internal endpoints: the telegram→user resolver
# (/api/system/resolve-telegram/<id>) and the trusted /api/chat user override
# (X-Zoe-User-Id). Must match zoe-data's ZOE_INTERNAL_TOKEN. On loopback zoe-data
# also accepts calls with NO token, so this may be left empty when the bot runs on
# the same box as zoe-data; set it if the bot ever runs off-box.
ZOE_INTERNAL_TOKEN=

# HOW LINKING WORKS: each user stores their numeric Telegram id in their Zoe
# profile (PUT /api/user/profile/telegram, session-authed as themselves). On each
# message the bot resolves the verified sender's id to that Zoe user and forwards
# the turn as them. Unlinked senders are told their numeric id and asked to set it
# in Zoe settings — they never reach the brain as a real user.
